</ul>

<h2>Bypassing Specific Detection Platforms</h2>
<p>Different AI detectors look for different patterns, so understanding each one can help you tailor your humanization approach.</p>

<h3>Turnitin</h3>
<p>Turnitin analyzes text at the sentence level and highlights sentences it believes are AI-generated. It tends to flag text with low perplexity — sentences that are too predictable. The solution is to add unexpected elements: unusual word choices, varied syntax, and specific details. Learn more in this detailed <a href="https://aifreetextpro.com/bypass-turnitin-ai-detection" rel="dofollow" target="_blank">Turnitin guide</a>.</p>

<h3>GPTZero</h3>
<p>GPTZero looks at both perplexity and burstiness across the entire document. It can flag content that''s too uniform in its sentence structure, even if individual sentences seem human-written. Adding paragraph-level variation — mixing short, punchy paragraphs with longer, more detailed ones — can help. See this <a href="https://aifreetextpro.com/bypass-gptzero-detection" rel="dofollow" target="_blank">GPTZero analysis</a> for specific strategies.</p>

<h3>Originality.AI</h3>
<p>Originality.AI is one of the most aggressive detectors and is popular with publishers and content agencies. It uses a combination of methods and tends to err on the side of flagging content as AI-generated. For content that needs to pass Originality.AI, more extensive humanization is usually required. Check out this <a href="https://aifreetextpro.com/bypass-originality-ai" rel="dofollow" target="_blank">Originality.AI guide</a> for detailed recommendations.</p>

